Red tide information: Concentration decreases in Pinellas, Manati and Sarassoc
The latest report from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Committee shows an overall decrease in red tide concentration in some parts of Tampa Bay.
According to the committee's information, individual places with flowering are reported in Pinellas, Manati, Sarasota, Charlotte and Calle districts, which means a decrease in concentration.
The "red tide" bloom stretches approximately 130 miles (200 km) of coastline from the northern part of Pinelas County to the southern part of Lee County.
Flowering chunks can be found about 10 miles (15 km) from the shore in Hillsbar County. but compared to last week, their number is decreasing.
"Red tide" has also been seen in Pasco County.
Concentrations of medium size on shore or near shore in the district of Pinelas were observed last week, in Hilsbar the concentration was low to high. in Manati about background to high, on shore or near shore in the district of Saratoga the concentration was from background to high in the district of Charlotte.
Irritation of respiratory tracts is reported from Pinellas, Manati, Sarasota, Lee and Calle districts.
Last week, there were no reports of respiratory tract irritation from Northwest Florida.
